  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_09_xi: This day I did come out of all my trouble.",
  "body": "This day I did come out of all my trouble. Nay I have cast out all my trouble; it should rather be for that which troubled thee, whatsoever it was, was not without anywhere that thou shouldest come out of it, but within in thine own opinions, from whence it must be cast out, before thou canst truly and constantly be at ease.",
